WEBVTT

I01
00:00:03.670 --> 00:00:11.693
Improve Agent lets you describe a change directly or include chats that demonstrate the correction.

I02
00:00:11.413 --> 00:00:19.614
Choose From chats, describe the billing-first change, and attach the correction conversation to show the new behavior.

I03
00:00:19.334 --> 00:00:27.218
Check the billing-first correction, the behaviors that must stay intact, and the checks OpenPond will rerun.

I04
00:00:26.938 --> 00:00:33.212
Review the planned change and confirm that it preserves citations and every existing action.

I05
00:00:32.932 --> 00:00:42.157
Compare both versions with the same checks: the current Agent passes four of five, while the updated Agent passes all six.

I06
00:00:41.877 --> 00:00:49.850
Apply the update only after that comparison. The existing Agent updates in place, with the successful checks recorded.

I07
00:00:49.570 --> 00:00:58.924
The improved chat now places disputed billing and the open P1 case ahead of adoption decline while preserving source citations.

I08
00:00:58.644 --> 00:01:07.371
The direct triage action repeats the billing-first result, proving the change works outside chat without breaking the existing workflow.
